<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="301" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="301">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="301">
This genus occurs in the Australasian and Neotropical regions, with more than 100 described species (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/0165052050014061" author="Manzo, V" journalOrPublisher="Studies on Neotropical Fauna and Environment" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="201 - 208" refId="B57" refString="Manzo, V, 2005. Key to the South America genera of Elmidae (Insecta: Coleoptera) with distributional data. Studies on Neotropical Fauna and Environment 40 (3): 201 - 208, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/0165052050014061" title="Key to the South America genera of Elmidae (Insecta: Coleoptera) with distributional data." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/0165052050014061" volume="40" year="2005">Manzo 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Manzo, V" journalOrPublisher="Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="11 - 20" publicationUrl="https://www.redalyc.org/pdf/3220/322028490003.pdf" refId="B58" refString="Manzo, V, 2007. Cinco citas nuevas de Elmidae (Coleoptera) para la Argentina, con la redescripcion de Austrolimnius (Telmatelmis) nyctelioides. Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina 66 (1-2): 11 - 20, https://www.redalyc.org/pdf/3220/322028490003.pdf" title="Cinco citas nuevas de Elmidae (Coleoptera) para la Argentina, con la redescripcion de Austrolimnius (Telmatelmis) nyctelioides." url="https://www.redalyc.org/pdf/3220/322028490003.pdf" volume="66" year="2007">2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1163/9789004291775" author="Jaech, MA" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" refId="B49" refString="Jaech, MA, Kodada, J, Brojer, M, Shepard, W, Ciampor, JrF, 2016. Coleoptera: Elmidae and Protelmidae. World Catalogue of Insects. Vol.14. Brill, Leiden, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1163/9789004291775" title="Coleoptera: Elmidae and Protelmidae. World Catalogue of Insects. Vol. 14." url="https://doi.org/10.1163/9789004291775" year="2016">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Jäch">Jaech</normalizedToken>
et al. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). Twenty species of this genus have been recorded in the Americas, from northern Mexico through southeastern Argentina (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-3113.1971.tb00110.x" author="Hinton, HE" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Entomology (B)" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="93 - 99" refId="B46" refString="Hinton, HE, 1971. Some American Austrolimnius (Coleoptera: Elmidae). Journal of Entomology (B) 40 (2): 93 - 99, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-3113.1971.tb00110.x" title="Some American Austrolimnius (Coleoptera: Elmidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-3113.1971.tb00110.x" volume="40" year="1971">Hinton 1971</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Manzo, V" journalOrPublisher="Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="11 - 20" publicationUrl="https://www.redalyc.org/pdf/3220/322028490003.pdf" refId="B58" refString="Manzo, V, 2007. Cinco citas nuevas de Elmidae (Coleoptera) para la Argentina, con la redescripcion de Austrolimnius (Telmatelmis) nyctelioides. Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina 66 (1-2): 11 - 20, https://www.redalyc.org/pdf/3220/322028490003.pdf" title="Cinco citas nuevas de Elmidae (Coleoptera) para la Argentina, con la redescripcion de Austrolimnius (Telmatelmis) nyctelioides." url="https://www.redalyc.org/pdf/3220/322028490003.pdf" volume="66" year="2007">Manzo 2007</bibRefCitation>
), with four species recorded from Mexico (
<bibRefCitation author="Santiago-Fragoso, S" editor="Llorente-Bousquets, J" journalOrPublisher="CONABIO and UNAM, Mexico City" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="421 - 438" publicationUrl="https://www.biotaxa.org/RSEA/article/view/33624" refId="B86" refString="Santiago-Fragoso, S, Spangler, PJ, 1995. Elmidae (Coleoptera). In: Llorente-Bousquets, J, Garcia-Aldrete, AN, Gonzalez-Soriano, E, Eds., Biodiversidad, taxonomia y biogeografia de artropodos de Mexico: hacia una sintesis de su conocimiento. CONABIO and UNAM, Mexico City: 421 - 438, https://www.biotaxa.org/RSEA/article/view/33624" title="Elmidae (Coleoptera)." url="https://www.biotaxa.org/RSEA/article/view/33624" volumeTitle="Biodiversidad, taxonomia y biogeografia de artropodos de Mexico: hacia una sintesis de su conocimiento." year="1995">Santiago-Fragoso and Spangler 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1163/9789004291775" author="Jaech, MA" journalOrPublisher="Brill, Leiden" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" refId="B49" refString="Jaech, MA, Kodada, J, Brojer, M, Shepard, W, Ciampor, JrF, 2016. Coleoptera: Elmidae and Protelmidae. World Catalogue of Insects. Vol.14. Brill, Leiden, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1163/9789004291775" title="Coleoptera: Elmidae and Protelmidae. World Catalogue of Insects. Vol. 14." url="https://doi.org/10.1163/9789004291775" year="2016">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Jäch">Jaech</normalizedToken>
et al. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
